SIMPLE: uncock
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncock
<hw>Un*cock"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>cock</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To let down
the cock of, as a firearm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deprive of its cocked shape, as a hat,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To open or spread from a cock or heap, as
hay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncoffle</ent>⟦br⟧
